# Polymarket Weather Trading Bot — Environment Variables
#
# Copy to .env and fill in.  Then: chmod 600 .env
#
# Security:
#   1. Use a DEDICATED wallet — never your main wallet
#   2. Only deposit USDC you can afford to lose
#   3. Never commit .env

# Polymarket proxy / Gnosis Safe address (the wallet that holds your USDC).
# If you registered on polymarket.com and deposited USDC there, your funds
# live in a proxy / Safe wallet — paste its address here.  Find it at
# polymarket.com → Profile → Wallet (the "Polymarket address" line).
# When set, ClobClient signs orders with signature_type=2 (POLY_GNOSIS_SAFE).
# Leave as the literal placeholder ``0x`` (or empty) for direct EOA mode
# (signature_type=0) — used when the private key itself holds USDC.
FUNDER_ADDRESS=0x

# Optional: HMAC token protecting the dashboard /api/admin/* and
# /api/trigger endpoints.  Required for live mode if you intend to
# pause/resume from the dashboard or external automation.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -hex 32
TRIGGER_SECRET=

# Optional: custom Polygon RPC endpoint.  Reserved for future on-chain
# helpers (settlement redemption, balance queries) — currently unused.
# Defaults to polygon-rpc.com when not set.
POLYGON_RPC_URL=

# Optional: webhook URL for trade / circuit-breaker alerts
# (Discord, Slack, or Telegram bot endpoint).
ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=

# Optional: NWS / Open-Meteo are the primary forecast sources; if you
# also want OpenWeatherMap as a fallback, drop the key here.
OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY=

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT NEEDED — auto-derived at runtime:
#   ETH_PRIVATE_KEY        — loaded from macOS Keychain
#                            (service=polymarket-bot, account=private-key,
#                            shared with the polymarket trade bot)
#   POLYMARKET_API_KEY     — derived from the private key on first run via
#   POLYMARKET_SECRET        py-clob-client.create_or_derive_api_creds().
#   POLYMARKET_PASSPHRASE    Free, deterministic, signs once with L1 key.
#
# Pre-populating any of POLYMARKET_API_KEY/SECRET/PASSPHRASE still works
# (back-compat) and short-circuits the derive call.  ETH_PRIVATE_KEY is
# only consulted as a fallback for non-macOS deploys (VPS paper today).
